  "prompt": "How do artists who work under anonymous pseudonyms report their taxes?",
  "response": "Artists working under anonymous pseudonyms typically report their taxes just like other self-employed individuals or independent contractors. They would:\n\n1. Use their legal name and Social Security Number/Tax ID\n2. Report income through standard tax forms like 1099s\n3. File Schedule C for self-employment income\n4. Maintain separate bank accounts for professional earnings\n5. Keep detailed records of income and expenses\n\nTheir legal identity is used for tax purposes, while their professional pseudonym remains separate from their tax documentation.",
